        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-04-22T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-04-22T20:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/4–2349: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clark</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-04-23T09:00:00+08:00">April 23, 1949—9 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 23—1:03 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Cantel 254. Received today urgent FonOff note referring note January 25 and
                    urging that because Nanking has become war area, Embassy take action move Canton
                    as requested previous note.</p>
                <p>Sent Department, repeated Nanking 213.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
